          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.His203Thrfs*50) in the PCNT gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in PCNT are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 18174396, 22821869). This variant is present in population databases (rs767416279, gnomAD 0.0009%). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with PCNT-related conditions. ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (Variation ID: 915399). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
